snippet: Early troubles under the Affordable Care Act are expected to be replaced by new difficulties as insurance prices fluctuate and more people sign up.
abstract: Health insurance executives and managers of online insurance marketplaces are girding for coming open enrollment period, saying they fear it could be even more difficult than the first one; consumers will face wide swings in prices and will have shorter time frame for choosing new policy.
lead_paragraph: Early troubles under the Affordable Care Act are expected to be replaced by new difficulties as insurance prices fluctuate and more people sign up.

headline.main: Bracing for New Challenges in Year 2 of Health Care Law
